         <abstract>
            <p>This paper contains graphs and tables of the function $$^{Ai}_{p,q}(\alpha,x) = \int^\infty_{-\infty}(2\pi)^{-1} \exp\{iy^p/p-\alpha y^q/q + ixy\} dy$$ and its indefinite integral for $p = 3, 5, 7$, for $q = 2, 4, 6$ and for several values of $\alpha$ with $\alpha \geqslant 0$. It is shown how these tables should influence the choice of an artificial viscosity for a difference scheme for a linear hyperbolic equation.</p>
          </abstract>
